<div id="review_2232706184" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2232706184" />
    <a title="Kevin Bunick" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/68297198-kevin-bunick"><img alt="Kevin Bunick" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1504556964p2/68297198.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2232706184?book_show_action=true">Jan 04, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kevin Bunick" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kevin Bunick" href="/user/show/68297198-kevin-bunick">Kevin Bunick</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2232706184" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5294076436754899757">If you suffer from anxiety, especially over everyday occurrences or seemingly trivial matters (like me), you should find this book extremely helpful. I did not expect it to be a 2,000 year old self-help book when I choose it, but voila! It focuses on explaining how to release things out of your control, albeit in a logical format. It&apos;s like an ancient &quot;Don&apos;t sweat the small stuff&quot; presented in philosophical arguments. Don&apos;t be scared off because you think it might be a difficult read because it&apos;</span>
  <span id="freeText5294076436754899757" style="display:none">If you suffer from anxiety, especially over everyday occurrences or seemingly trivial matters (like me), you should find this book extremely helpful. I did not expect it to be a 2,000 year old self-help book when I choose it, but voila! It focuses on explaining how to release things out of your control, albeit in a logical format. It's like an ancient "Don't sweat the small stuff" presented in philosophical arguments. Don't be scared off because you think it might be a difficult read because it's super approachable, although dry. Oh, and I learned about Stoicism as well, which is why I selected it in the first place. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5294076436754899757" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
