        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2199144690" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16351051394088313512">The first time I tried to read Epictetus&apos; Discourses, I couldn&apos;t finish it. Do you know why? Because by chapter 29 out of 90 I had heard, for the third or forth time, how Epictetus would reply if one commanded him to shave himself. His musings on stoicism are thoroughly profound, I admit, but I couldn&apos;t put up with a philosopher droning on about the same thing ad nauseam. The book seemed boring and repetitive, and I eventually found myself taking shorter and shorter routes to work so that I coul</span>
  <span id="freeText16351051394088313512" style="display:none">The first time I tried to read Epictetus' Discourses, I couldn't finish it. Do you know why? Because by chapter 29 out of 90 I had heard, for the third or forth time, how Epictetus would reply if one commanded him to shave himself. His musings on stoicism are thoroughly profound, I admit, but I couldn't put up with a philosopher droning on about the same thing ad nauseam. The book seemed boring and repetitive, and I eventually found myself taking shorter and shorter routes to work so that I could end my daily stoicism earlier.<br /><br />A second read made me swallow my previous words.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16351051394088313512" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

