              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8064167156872854127">His discourse on the use of the forms of right reasoning is a survey with concluding opinon. We haven&apos;t gone far from his understanding of the fundamental ground of reasoning. Worth a read, but probably not the complete works in a number of volumes unless you are a philosopher or a glutten for philosophical minutiae. I am neither. I think it an important work in my own grounding.</span>
